# ğŸ“ Video Summary Evaluation Web App

This is a lightweight web interface for conducting user studies on video summary quality. Participants watch videos and evaluate AI- or human-generated summaries.

---

## ğŸš€ Getting Started

### âœ… 1. Install Node.js and npm (via `nvm`)

Make sure you have Node.js (version **â‰¥20**) installed:

```bash
# Install nvm if you haven't already
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

# Load nvm in the current terminal session
export NVM_DIR="$([ -z "${XDG_CONFIG_HOME-}" ] && printf %s "${HOME}/.nvm" || printf %s "${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/nvm")"
[ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ] && \. "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh"

# Install and use Node.js 20
nvm install 20
nvm use 20

# Confirm version
node -v  # Should output v20.x.x
npm -v
```

---

### âœ… 2. Install dependencies

In the project root:

```bash
npm install
```

---

### âœ… 3. Start the app locally

```bash
npm run dev
```

The app will be available at:  
ğŸ‘‰ `http://localhost:5173/`

---

## ğŸ‘¤ Adding New Users

To add a new user for the study:

1. Go to the folder: `./public/user_data/`
2. Create a new folder with the user ID (e.g., `user11`)
3. Inside that folder, add the following three summary files:
   - `gama.txt`
   - `llama.txt`
   - `human.txt`

Each file should contain one version of the summary for the user.

---

## ğŸ¥ Adding New Videos

### Step 1: Upload to YouTube

- Upload the short and long versions of your video
- Set each video to **â€œUnlistedâ€**
- Copy the video ID from the YouTube URL (i.e., the part after `youtu.be/` or `watch?v=`)

### Step 2: Register in `videoMap.js`

Edit: `./src/data/videoMap.js`

Add a new entry for the user like this:

```js
const VIDEO_URLS = {
  user11: {
    short: "https://www.youtube.com/embed/yourShortVideoID",
    long:  "https://www.youtube.com/embed/yourLongVideoID"
  },
  // ... other users
};
```

